title: Response to site visit report SV29356
metadata_json:
{"compliance_id": "bb36b394-1edf-ef11-a372-0050568a2d1a", "document_type": "Site Updates/Notifications", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/LicenseeReturns/byid?lr_id=bb36b394-1edf-ef11-a372-0050568a2d1a", "title": "Response to site visit report SV29356", "description": "Good afternoon

The following information is provided in response to site visit report SV29356:

1) Copy of the site drawing showing the extent of the area covered by the CPO attached. Please note that the CPO process has not yet been implemented in full yet. We understand that Louth County Council has fully implemented all the steps in the CPO process for other nearby lands under the ownership of other landowners.

2) Update to planning application (reference 2460674): The outcome of the application is still pending. Louth County Council requested further information on 17th December 2024. The company is currently preparing the additional information for submission to the Council.

3) Copy of the 2024 Waste Register is attached as requested.

4) The ELRA & CRAMP for the installation will be updated in line with future activities once the outcome of the planning application is known.", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{"licenseereturnid": "bb36b394-1edf-ef11-a372-0050568a2d1a", "type": "Site Updates/Notifications", "reference": "LR090489", "subject": "Site Updates/Notifications:Response to EPA Report", "status": "Closed", "licenceid": "ed55f5d2-4492-40af-a0bf-a520970145e0", "licenceprofileid": "e3d4cdd5-7ad0-4785-83af-614411710884", "datereceived": "2025-01-30T00:00:00", "closeddate": "2025-06-24T00:00:00", "title": "Response to site visit report SV29356", "doctype": "Site Updates/Notifications", "docsubtype": "Response to EPA Report", "decision": "Assessed", "description": "Good afternoon\r\n\r\nThe following information is provided in response to site visit report SV29356:\r\n\r\n1) Copy of the site drawing showing the extent of the area covered by the CPO attached. Please note that the CPO process has not yet been implemented in full yet. We understand that Louth County Council has fully implemented all the steps in the CPO process for other nearby lands under the ownership of other landowners.\r\n\r\n2) Update to planning application (reference 2460674): The outcome of the application is still pending. Louth County Council requested further information on 17th December 2024. The company is currently preparing the additional information for submission to the Council.\r\n\r\n3) Copy of the 2024 Waste Register is attached as requested.\r\n\r\n4) The ELRA & CRAMP for the installation will be updated in line with future activities once the outcome of the planning application is known.", "documentcategory": null, "complianceinvestigationid": null}"}

The Fire Water Retention report was subsequently revised and resubmitted to the Agency on 30/06/2022 under licence return LR069006 where the material was reclassified in the report as Low Risk Combustible material. From our understanding the revised description was accepted and the query was closed. {"compliance_id": "4fd6a2a0-33b5-449d-95c7-27a24c0f0cab", "document_type": "Meeting", "document_url": "https://data.epa.ie/leap/api/v1/MeetingCorrespondence/meetingbyid?meeting_id=4fd6a2a0-33b5-449d-95c7-27a24c0f0cab", "title": "", "description": "", "submission_date": "", "status": "Closed", "metadata": "{\"meetingid\": \"4fd6a2a0-33b5-449d-95c7-27a24c0f0cab\", \"type\": \"Meeting\", \"reference\": \"MTG000746\", \"subject\": \"Ringsend WWTP upgrade project update from Uisce \\u00c9ireann\", \"status\": \"Closed\", \"meetingdate\": \"2025-04-07T00:00:00\", \"organisationid\": \"f5545f77-3749-e211-9eb5-0050568a69e2\", \"location\": \"Online MS Teams\", \"regarding\": \"Compliance Investigations\", \"meetingtime\": \"12:00\", \"attendeesepa\": \"Lorcan Farrell, Stephen McCarthy, David Shannon\", \"attendeesnoepa\": \"Uisce \\u00c9ireann: Ringsend WWTP Upgrade Project Team, Compliance Team & Asset Operations\\n\", \"actionitems\": \"

A video conference meeting was held between the EPA and Uisce Éireann (UÉ) on 08/04/2025 from 12:00 to 12:50 approx.

\\n

During the meeting UÉ gave an update to the EPA on the phased upgrades being undertaken at Ringsend WWTP and a summary of treatment plant performance for Q1 2025.

\\n

Works on Hybrid II upgrades and sludge treatment facilities are progressing as scheduled with all primary aspects of the upgrade project due for completion by end 2025. A programme of ancillary works connected with the overall upgrade project is also being progressed with most completion dates falling within 2025.

\\n

A summary of plant performance was given. UÉ are aiming for 104 compliance samples to be taken during 2025. 10 no. samples records were recorded in the Q1 Update under compliance investigation (CI000025).  Compliance results were unavailable for the first three weeks of January. This was attributed to operational reasons (plant shutdowns) and management changeover. It is UÉ’s intention to make up the shortfall to 104 compliance samples over the year. It was acknowledged that there is a risk that TN and TP average limits may not be achieved this year. UÉ expect that performance will improve across all parameters once remaining upgraded SBR blocks come back on-line and as average air temperatures increase through the year. UÉ confirmed that higher than expected load on the plant (2.17 PE in 2024) was expected to continue increasing in 2025 and is also affecting treatment performance. Issues with the aeration system in the Capital Upgrade treatment block were also cited as a compounding factor in treatment performance and should be resolved by end April 2025.

\\n

The EPA instructed Uisce Éireann to carry out all actions necessary to comply with the waste water discharge licence.

\", \"licenceid\": \"4ab24fc5-2bf8-4aa8-ad9e-f4f68c559186\", \"originalmeetingid\": \"0d83b2ed-7614-f011-a373-0050568a2d1a\", \"organisationname\": \"Uisce \\u00c9ireann\"}"}
